snippet.textDisplay:
He does need to get that defense up. However, I think future opponents will look at him like "he's easy to hit"...they may hit him...he may get hurt...but he'll keep fighting...his punch combination output is consistent all throughout a fight...and as a future elite fighter "hits" him...but if that fighter cannot put Munguia away, they'll tire out and Munguia's output will remain and could spell trouble for a future elite.

He's still got a lot of work to do, but a lot of promise and obviously popular with the attending crowd for the action. He'll just have to make sure he doesn't completely shorten his career by getting his defense on point and having a bit more of a controlled output when it's necessary.
